  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Site Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><ul><li>Comply with the local construction code and approved Quality document</li><li>Assist project teams to identify quality requirements and develop Project Quality Plans for projects</li><li>Conduct inspection reports for all subcontractors work to ensure alignment with the quality standards</li><li>Assist Project Teams with control vendor performance/non-conformance issues and implement actions to correct non-compliance</li><li>Prepare and submit Request for Inspection (RFI) to consultant prior to official QA/QC inspection and testing activity</li><li>Carry out the execution of the project as per plan</li><li>Register all incoming materials and items for the project</li><li>Responsible for managing day to day lifting operations</li><li>Plan, organize, supervise and liaise closely with sub-contractors and operation teams on all ongoing lifting activities</li><li>Conduct routine checks and inspections of works on site to ensure compliance with authorities' and client’s requirements</li><li>Review project safety</li><li>Other ad hoc duties as assigned</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent</li><li>At least 6 years of working experience in the related field is required</li><li>Ability to work with tight deadlines</li><li>Work closely with project team to resolve technical issues</li><li>Good attitude and communication skills</li><li>Willing to multi-task</li><li>Need to be stationed at site</li><li>Candidates with experience in building are preferred</li><li>Working days: 6 days</li><li>Fast-paced building project environment</li><li>Involvement in structural steel construction</li><li>Experience with precast concrete elements</li><li>Coordination and execution of external works</li></ul>",
